        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>This collection (of unknown provenance), was titled the French Anarchists Autograph Collection. However, it also contains signed letters of other European anarchists.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This is a collection of 25 signed letters, all but four in French, by European anarchists, mostly French: Fernand Brouez, Gabriel De La Salle, Henry Dupont, Sebastien Faure, Jean Grave, Pierre Kropotkin, Enrico Malatesta, Charles Malato, Louise Michel, David Nicole, Emile Pouget, Felix Pyat, Elisee Reclus, Henry Seymour, Wilhelm Spohr, Laurent Tailhade, and S. Yanovsky.</p>
            <p>Patrons must wear gloves, and may only be given one document at a time. INVENTORY AVAILABLE IN REPOSITORY; CONTACT: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
        </scopecontent>
